iguration tests**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to configure tests with TestSslEngine and how RecordingSslConnection extends SslConnection. In the constructor, I’m questioning if calling `super(new ArrayByteBufferPool(), DIRECT_EXECUTOR, new ByteArrayEndPoint(), sslEngine);` actually invokes some SSLEngine methods. It might not. I'm also considering whether `newDecryptedEndPoint` in the constructor could invoke session sizes, but maybe it doesn't have to. I’ll need to take a closer look at the DecryptedEndPoint constructor next.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FC7EhpJAsquyx0mISw4UNYjN|fc_033200bf85d7a50f016a01f8b52e948196afceb87edbb53808", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd $tmp; curl -fsSLO https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/eclipse/jetty/jetty-io/11.0.24/jetty-io-11.0.24-sources.jar && jar xf jetty-io-11.0.24-sources.jar org/eclipse/jetty/io/ssl/SslConnection.java && grep -n \"class DecryptedEndPoint\" -A90 org/eclipse/jetty/io/ssl/SslConnection.java | head -120", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1119, "output": 1560, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31351, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778514080159, "responseId": "resp_033200bf85d7a50f016a01f8a0aff08196a380984ae33cbbe9"}}
